{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "SB264", "title": "Impersonation of a peace officer or firefighter during a state of emergency or local emergency.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Impersonationofapeaceofficerorfirefighterduringastateofemergencyorlocalemergency"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing law, the California Emergency Services Act, authorizes the Governor to proclaim a state of emergency, as defined, under specified circumstances. Existing law makes it a misdemeanor to impersonate a peace officer or an officer or member of a fire department or the Office of the State Fire Marshal.\n\nThis bill would make impersonating a peace officer or an officer or member of a fire department or the Office of the State Fire Marshal during a state of emergency or local emergency punishable as either a misdemeanor or a felony, as specified. By increasing the punishment of a crime, this bill would impose a state-mandated local program.\n\nThe California Constitution requires the state to reimburse local agencies and school districts for certain costs mandated by the state. Statutory provisions establish procedures for making that reimbursement.\n\nThis bill would provide that no reimbursement is required by this act for a specified reason."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Introduced. Read first time. To Com. on RLS. for assignment. To print.", "date": "2025-02-03", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["introduction", "reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be acted upon on or after March 6.", "date": "2025-02-04", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on PUB. S.", "date": "2025-02-14", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["r